8%A7%D9%81%D9%8E"}}, "translations": {"en": "to add", "fa": "افزودن", "ur": "شامل کرنا", "tr": "eklemek", "id": "menambahkan", "bn": "যোগ করা", "es": "añadir", "fr": "ajouter", "de": "hinzufügen", "ru": "добавлять", "zh": "添加"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to add; to append; to attach"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/ʔa.dˤaː.fa/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n26207", "headword_ar": "اضاف", "root": "Dyf", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", intrans.: see 1, in three places. ―         -b2-  Also, said of a man,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He ran,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hastened, made haste,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sped,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ibn-'Abbád, O, K,) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fled,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1814}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "turned away and fled:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) and said of a dog as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he ran away,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fled."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jbn", "text_ar": "جبن"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ADAf EalaY Al$~aYo'i", "text_ar": "اضاف عَلَى الشَّىْءِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$orafa Ealayohi", "text_ar": "اَشْرَفَ عَلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He looked upon,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "viewed, the thing from above:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he was,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became, on the brink,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "verge,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "at the point, of the thing:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.]. (O, K, * TA.) ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tuDiyfu A_ilaY Sawoti AlfaHoli", "text_ar": "تُضِيفُ اـِلَى صَوْتِ الفَحْلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", said of a she-camel, means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "She hears with desire of going to him the voice,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sound, of the stallion."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M.) ―         -b5-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA_iDaAfapu", "text_ar": "الاـِضَافَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alt~aDaAyufu", "text_ar": "التَّضَايُفُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Correlation,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "reciprocal relation, so that one of the two cannot be conceived in the mind without the other;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as in the case of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^ubuw~apu", "text_ar": "الاُبُوَّةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Albunuw~apu", "text_ar": "البُنُوَّةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. fathership and sonship]. (KT. [See also 3.])       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ADAfhu A_ilayohi", "text_ar": "اضافهُ اـِلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He made it to incline towards it;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, * O, Msb, K; *) namely, a thing (S, O) to a thing. (S, O, Msb.)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He made it to lean, rest,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "stay itself, against it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon it."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, TA.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ADAf Zahorahu A_ilaY AlHaAy^iTi", "text_ar": "اضاف ظَهْرَهُ اـِلَى الحَايِطِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He leaned his back against the wall."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(MA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "ADAf A_ilayohi A^amorFA", "text_ar": "اضاف اـِلَيْهِ اَمْرًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He rested,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "stayed, upon him an affair, and desired him to do what would suffice."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b2-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He made him to have recourse to it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to betake himself to it for refuge."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, K.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He adjoined it to it."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) ―         -b4-  And hence"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA_iDaAfapu", "text_ar": "الاـِضَافَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as a conventional term of the grammarians; because the first [of two nouns in the case to which it applies] is adjoined to the second: (Msb:) [for]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iDaAfapu AlAisomi A_ilaY AlAisomi", "text_ar": "اـِضَافَةُ الاِسْمِ اـِلَى الاِسْمِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The prefixing the noun to the noun so that the former governs the latter in the gen. case"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] as when you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gulaAmu zayodK", "text_ar": "غُلَامُ زَيْدٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; in which instance,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "glAm", "text_ar": "غلام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is termed ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muDaAfN", "text_ar": "مُضَافٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zyd", "text_ar": "زيد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ilayohi", "text_ar": "اـِلَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muDaAfN", "text_ar": "مُضَافٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and this is done for the purpose of particularizing or appropriating, and of making known or definite: therefore the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iDaAfap", "text_ar": "اـِضَافَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a thing to itself [i. e. the prefixing a noun in this manner to one identical therewith in meaning] is not allowable, because a thing does not make known, or definite, itself; (S;) unless by an ellipsis, as when you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haq~u Alyaqiyni", "text_ar": "حَقُّ اليَقِينِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Haq~u Al$~aYo'i Alyaqiyni", "text_ar": "حَقُّ الشَّىْءِ اليَقِينِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; or, accord. to Fr, the Arabs used to do so because of the difference of the two words themselves. (S voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jaAmiEN", "text_ar": "جَامِعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA_iDaAfapu", "text_ar": "الاـِضَافَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also often used as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The state of being prefixed in the manner explained above;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the connection of a noun so prefixed with its complement."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "The various kinds of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iDaAfap", "text_ar": "اـِضَافَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "are sufficiently explained in the grammars of De Sacy and others: they are not proper subjects of a lexicon, though much is said respecting them in the O, and more in the Msb. ―         -b5-  Hence also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biAlA_iDaAfapi A_ilaY ka*aA", "text_ar": "بِالاـِضَافَةِ اـِلَى كَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "In comparison with"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "), or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in relation to,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biAln~isobapi A_ilaY", "text_ar": "بِالنِّسْبَةِ اـِلَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such a thing;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as though"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in juxtaposition to it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "a phrase of frequent occurrence: see an ex. in Bd ii. 6.] ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aDafotuhu", "text_ar": "اَضَفْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_iDaAfapN", "text_ar": "اـِضَافَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", Msb) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Day~afotuhu", "text_ar": "ضَيَّفْتُهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taDoyiyfN", "text_ar": "تَضْيِيفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", O) both signify the same, (S, M, O, Msb, K,) from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlD~iyaAfapu", "text_ar": "الضِّيَافَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (O;) i. e. both signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I made him a guest,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "lodged him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "gave him refuge"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "asylum,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^anozalotuhu", "text_ar": "اَنْزَلْتُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with me, as a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Dayof", "text_ar": "ضَيْف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "guest"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (S,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and entertained him:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M, Msb:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aDaAfuwhu", "text_ar": "اَضَافُوهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Day~afuwhu", "text_ar": "ضَيَّفُوهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "both signify"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_b